// An error is a problem that occurs while JavaScript code is being parsed or executed.

// types of errors

//     syntax errors 
//     runtime errors
//     logical errors

// Runtime vs Logical Error Difference
// Runtime errors crash execution and throw exceptions (like undefinedVariable.property). Logical errors run silently but give incorrect output (like sum += i in wrong loop condition). Runtime = crash; Logical = wrong result.

